		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Sumez wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't think I disagree (it can really go both ways), but why is it specifically a good thing that it was written by Americans?</div><br />Japan has its own way of telling vampire stories. See for example JoJo's Bizarre Adventure or Symphony of the Night.<br /><br />But Castlevania 1 and 3 were not based on Japanese vampires; they were based on Western ones. By having American writers the show is going to feel more like Bram Stoker's novel and less like Shonen Jump.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
