	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Castlevania games are Japanese-made though, and have always been more Bram Stoker-style and less Jojo Shounen Jump-style.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">according to the CV3 storyline, this game is the first one when a Belmont encountered Dracula. So, I'm asking myself if the TV series plays after the events of the game instead of depicting the game's events themselves.</div><br />When CV3 was released it was the earliest account of a Belmont killing Dracula. But several Castlevania games that take place before it have been release since that, both canon (Lament of Innocence ) and non-canon (Castlevania Legend). Dracula is able to revive every 100 years.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


